```julia
using Dates

function timezone_bumper(dt::DateTime; bump = 3)
    return dt + Hour(bump)
end

@testset "Testing timezone_bumper function" begin
    dt1 = DateTime("2022-01-01T15:00:00")
    @test timezone_bumper(dt1, 3) == DateTime("2022-01-01T18:00:00")
    @test_throws ErrorException timezone_bumper(Date("2022-01-01"))
end
```

In the test case provided, the `timezone_bumper` function is tested with a DateTime object and a Date object. The test is ensured to pass by comparing the result of the function call with the expected output. If the function raises an error when trying to convert a Date type instead of a DateTime type, the `@test_throws` macro will catch this error and consider the test as passed. 

Replace "2022-01-01T15:00:00" with any date and time you would like to test the function.
